otis tenuifolia include flavonoids, alkaloids, and phenolic acids, which contribute to its medicinal properties. In traditional Chinese medicine, Hedyotis tenuifolia is commonly prepared as a decoction, tablet, or capsule, and is also used to make a tea or tincture, making it a versatile and accessible herbal remedy."}